A maximal simplex is a simplex that is not a proper face of any other simplex in the simplicial complex. In the given simplicial complex K, we have the following simplices:

1. {v1, v2, v3}
2. {v2, v3, v4}
3. {v1, v3, v4}

None of these simplices are proper faces of any other simplex in K. Therefore, all three simplices are maximal simplices.

The number of maximal simplices in K is 3.
